cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on software metrics for smart contracts and their differences from traditional software development. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as smart contracts are often used in blockchain-based systems which have security implications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper mentions the different languages in which smart contracts can be written. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as smart contracts run on a distributed blockchain infrastructure. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions downloading smart contract code from a public repository.
